EbookNT — Summary of Modifications
====================================

EbookNT is a fork of Document Viewer
(https://github.com/SufficientlySecure/document-viewer), which itself
derives from the last GPL-licensed version of EBookDroid.

All modifications listed below were made by the EbookNT maintainer(s)
starting from Document Viewer commit c9bcd308 ("fix Spanish translation
xml errors").  The original project could no longer build on modern
toolchains or run on modern Android; EbookNT is effectively a rewrite of
the build system and substantial portions of the UI and runtime code.

The full, per-file change history is available via `git log`.


Build & Toolchain
-----------------
- Migrated Gradle wrapper and build scripts to support Java 17/21.
- Updated target/compile SDK for modern Android (API 33+).
- Absorbed git submodules (MuPDF, DjVuLibre, etc.) into a single
  monolithic repository to simplify builds.
- Upgraded MuPDF from 1.11 to 1.14, including all third-party
  dependencies (freetype, harfbuzz, libjpeg, openjpeg, mujs, etc.).
- Integrated the native (NDK) build into Gradle via
  externalNativeBuild; no separate ndk-build step required.


Application Identity
--------------------
- Renamed from "Document Viewer" to "EbookNT".
- Changed application ID (package name) to org.ebooknt.viewer.
- Redesigned application icon and logo.


Network & Permissions
---------------------
- Removed OPDS catalog support and the INTERNET permission entirely.
  The application is 100% offline.


User Interface
--------------
- Redesigned the Recent/Library/Browser navigation flow with a
  toolbar spinner for switching between Recent and File Browser views.
- Added a navigation drawer listing all currently open books.
- Added support for multiple simultaneously open books, switchable
  from the drawer.
- Reworked the search UI to avoid layout overlap between pathname and
  file size; integrated instant-search into the PDF outline.
- Redesigned the "Go to page" dialog: compact layout, positioned at
  the bottom of the screen to stay out of the reading area.
- Reworked the fullscreen reading experience: double-tap behavior,
  fast-pagination indicator, and status-bar/navigation-bar handling.
- Added desktop shortcut creation for individual books.
- Replaced the "bookcase" web-image placeholders with a static
  fallback for empty shelves.
- E-ink display support: adapted toolbar colors, drawer backgrounds,
  icon tinting, and dialog styling for e-ink screens.
- Configurable UI font scale.
- Extensive Chinese (Simplified and Traditional) translation
  corrections, plus additions/corrections for all 16 supported locales.
- Renamed user-visible "folder" terminology to "directory" across all
  locales (Android is not Windows).
- Added an "Exit the app" option to the main UI menu.
- Removed "Share" and "Open with" menu actions.


Library & File Browser
----------------------
- Simplified the library path from a colon-separated multi-path set
  to a single directory path; "Set as library" overwrites rather than
  appends.
- Added a graphical folder-picker dialog for selecting the library
  path in Settings, replacing the raw text-input field.
- Removed the real-time FileObserver-based filesystem watcher
  (persistent inotify watches caused unnecessary battery drain).
- Removed the associated "show notifications" preference (dead code
  after FileObserver removal).
- Removed the "Set as library" context-menu action from the file
  browser (redundant with the Settings folder picker).
- Non-existent library paths are no longer silently accepted.
- Fixed file-browser root listing on modern Android where
  File("/").listFiles() returns null: enumerate storage volumes via
  the StorageManager API instead.
- Book thumbnails in file-browser listings.
- Restored Home and Library navigation actions in the file-browser
  toolbar.


Text Selection & Dictionary
----------------------------
- Long-press to select text with draggable handles.
- Selected text can be looked up in external dictionary apps
  (ColorDict, GoldenDict, Google Translate, etc.).
- Works across all view modes (scroll, single-page) and on e-ink
  devices.


PDF Outline & Rendering
-----------------------
- Rewrote PDF outline (table-of-contents) loading to minimize JNI
  round-trips, significantly improving performance on large documents.
- Picture enhancement with live preview: dedicated settings screen
  with real-time preview of the current page; sliders for contrast,
  gamma, exposure, auto-levels, threshold, and smoothness.
- Improved auto-levels algorithm: histogram stretching is now applied
  before other adjustments, and uses asymmetric clipping for better
  results on scanned documents.
- Thread-safe native rendering context management.


Power & Battery
---------------
- GLSurfaceView is now properly paused/resumed with the Activity
  lifecycle, preventing the GL thread from holding the EGL context
  and running in the background.
- ScrollEventThread switches to a 5-second sleep interval when
  paused, instead of polling every second.
- Removed the persistent FileObserver (inotify) watcher that woke
  the process on any filesystem event in scanned directories.
- Screen-on (wake lock) capability is preserved for active reading.


Settings & Preferences
----------------------
- Book-template support: apply a set of default settings to newly
  opened books.
- Removed several obsolete preferences (auto-scan removable media,
  show scan dirs, show notifications) that no longer had backing code.
- Fixed a crash when switching view modes in book settings.


Cropping
--------
- Manual crop: visible OK/Cancel buttons and improved dialog
  layout.
- Manual crop: per-book default crop action — choose once and
  the dialog is skipped on subsequent uses; clearable per book.
- Manual crop: page alignment, zoom, and crop state are properly
  saved and restored across crop/cancel operations.
- Autocrop: conservative clamping — cropped bounds retain at
  least 2/3 of the original page width and height, preventing
  extreme zoom on sparse pages.


DjVu
----
- Added logical page-number detection for DjVu documents via
  JNI bridge to ddjvu_document_search_pageno().  The page-label
  offset is now auto-detected at load time, matching the existing
  PDF behavior.


Open Books & Navigation Drawer
-------------------------------
- Drawer now shows file-page numbers (e.g. "42/514") instead of
  percentage.
- Drawer "home" icon replaced with the EbookNT application icon.
- Proper landscape layout and improved overlay behavior (drawer
  no longer masks the reading page or conflicts with edge swipes).
- Multi-book caching: switch between open books instantly without
  re-decoding; configurable cache size.
- Improved book-close, flush, and app-exit lifecycle.


Search
------
- Progressive/asynchronous directory search: results appear
  incrementally as the file tree is traversed.
- Distinct search button labels per context: "Search History"
  (Recent view) vs. "Search Current Directory" (Browser view),
  across all 16 supported locales.


Outline & Page Navigation
-------------------------
- Added an outline drawer (left-edge swipe) with instant search
  filtering, optional preview mode, and a confirm/cancel workflow
  for navigating to entries.
- Added fast-scroll thumb to outline list for documents with
  many entries.
- Tree-structured navigation history: tracks page jumps as a
  tree rather than a linear stack; includes a visualization dialog.
- Enhanced "Go to page" dialog.


Rendering & Display
-------------------
- Replaced GLSurfaceView with TextureView for the document
  viewer, with explicit EGL lifecycle management.
- Simplified Rotate settings.
- Added Text Selection toggle in both global and per-book
  settings.
- Added scroll behavior settings (configurable scroll direction
  and sensitivity).


Localization
------------
- Manual-crop dialog strings translated across all locales
  (previously displayed in English only).
- Traditional Chinese (zh-rTW): updated to Taiwan-common
  terminology.
- Various Chinese translation corrections.


Tooling
-------
- Added tools/debug-monitor.sh: unified ADB-based crash and
  black-screen monitor.  Runs on the development PC; detects
  crashes via logcat filtering and black screens via periodic
  screenshot analysis; automatically dumps diagnostics
  (thread traces, activity/window/gfxinfo state) on events.
- Added crash logging support for debug builds.


Bug Fixes
---------
- Fixed PendingIntent missing FLAG_IMMUTABLE (crash on Android 12+).
- Fixed missing Notification Channel (crash on Android 8+).
- Added null-safety for EXT_STORAGE on devices without external
  storage.
- Fixed redundant file-copy behavior.
- Fixed fast-page-scroll floating info not updating promptly.
- Various other stability and correctness fixes throughout.
